  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Van driver",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary:<br>\n</strong>We are looking for a dependable and efficient Logistics Van Driver to support our supply chain operations by delivering goods to clients and distribution centers. The ideal candidate has experience in logistics or delivery services, excellent time management skills, and a strong commitment to safety and customer satisfaction.</p>\n<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:<br>\n<br>\n</strong>Transport goods and materials to various locations, including warehouses, retailers, and customer addresses.<br>\nLoad and unload items from the van, ensuring safe handling and securing of goods.<br>\nVerify delivery documentation such as invoices, manifests, and delivery notes.<br>\nPlan daily routes based on delivery schedules, using GPS and logistics software.<br>\nInspect vehicle regularly to ensure it is in proper working condition (fuel, tires, lights, etc.).<br>\nReport any delays, accidents, or issues with deliveries to the logistics coordinator or dispatcher.<br>\nMaintain accurate delivery logs, mileage records, and fuel receipts.<br>\nEnsure all items are delivered in good condition and obtain customer signatures upon delivery.<br>\nAdhere to company policies, road safety regulations, and health &amp; safety standards.<br>\nSupport loading and inventory activities at the warehouse when needed.</p>\n<p><strong>Requirements:<br>\n<br>\n</strong>Valid class 3 driver’s license.<br>\nPrevious experience in a logistics, courier.<br>\nExcellent knowledge of local and regional routes.<br>\nFamiliarity with handheld scanners, route planning apps, and basic paperwork.<br>\nStrong organizational and time management skills.<br>\nProfessional attitude and good communication skills.</p>",
